title._content: Brazil, Atlantic Ocean, Africa and Antarctica seen from Apollo 4

description._content: Collection: NASA Image eXchange Collection Title: Brazil, Atlantic Ocean, Africa and Antarctica seen from Apollo 4 Description: Coastal Brazil, Atlantic Ocean, West Africa, and Antarctica, looking west, as seen from the earth-orbital Apollo 4 (Spacecraft 017/Saturn 501) unmanned space mission. This picture was taken when the Spacecraft 017 and the Saturn S-IVB (third) stage was orbiting the earth at an altitude of 9,544 nautical miles. Date: 11.09.1967 Credit: NASA Johnson Space Center (NASA-JSC) [ images.jsc.nasa.gov/ ] ID: AS04-01-580 UID: SPD-NIX-AS04-01-580 Original url: nix.ksc.nasa.gov/info?id=AS04-01-580&orgid=8 SOURCE: nasaimages.org/luna/servlet/detail/nasaNAS~2~2~1365~102767 Visit www.nasaimages.org for the most comprehensive compilation of NASA stills, film and video, created in partnership with Internet Archive.
